<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,400,940,966]" box="[189,400,940,966]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,400,940,966]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,400,940,966]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Brief description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1399,988,1130]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Monoecious. Receptacle consisting of a uniseriate multicellular axis extending into the appendage, bearing branches and antheridia born from corner cells. Unicellular buffer cells often present above the foot (
<figureCitation box="[252,446,1061,1087]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,304,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1399,304,1816]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 7. Hydrophilomyces spp., mature thalli. A–B. H. coneglianensis Speg. Thallus from female (A) and from male hosts (B). – C. H. digitatus F.Picard. – D–E. H. gracilis T.Majewski. – F–G. H. hamatus T.Majewski. Abbreviations: acc = accessory cell; bf = buffer cells. Scale bars: 50 µm. Photographs from slides ZMUC C-F-122709 (A), ZMUC C-F-124088 (B), ZMUC C-F-124274 (C), ZMUC C-F-124043 (D–F), and ZMUC C-F-124042 (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5828938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5828938/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 7A–C, F–G</figureCitation>
, bf). Perithecial outer wall including an elongated accessory cell on the outer side (
<figureCitation box="[198,327,1097,1124]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="49.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,304,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-12@49.[189,1399,304,1816]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Fig. 7. Hydrophilomyces spp., mature thalli. A–B. H. coneglianensis Speg. Thallus from female (A) and from male hosts (B). – C. H. digitatus F.Picard. – D–E. H. gracilis T.Majewski. – F–G. H. hamatus T.Majewski. Abbreviations: acc = accessory cell; bf = buffer cells. Scale bars: 50 µm. Photographs from slides ZMUC C-F-122709 (A), ZMUC C-F-124088 (B), ZMUC C-F-124274 (C), ZMUC C-F-124043 (D–F), and ZMUC C-F-124042 (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5828938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5828938/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 7D, G</figureCitation>
, acc), parallel to the longer ventral outer wall cell (w 
<subScript attach="left" box="[948,957,1116,1130]" fontSize="6" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">1</subScript>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,303,1164,1190]" box="[189,303,1164,1190]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1164,1190]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1164,1190]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[187,1398,1211,1347]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
The genus consists of 16 species, of which 
<quantity box="[697,755,1211,1238]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
Europe, five in 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1057,1211,1237]" name="Denmark" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Denmark</collectingCountry>
. The most recently described species are 
<taxonomicName box="[319,449,1248,1274]" class="Laboulbeniomycetes" family="Laboulbeniaceae" genus="Hydrophilomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="deflexus">
<emphasis box="[319,449,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">H. deflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Santamaria et al. 2020 a)" baseAuthorityName="Santamaria" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[503,924,1248,1274]" class="Laboulbeniomycetes" family="Laboulbeniaceae" genus="Hydrophilomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="riberae">
<emphasis box="[503,623,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">H. riberae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Santamaria S. &amp; David Cuesta-Segura A. &amp; Guardia L." box="[636,916,1248,1274]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="347 - 367" refId="ref221022" refString="Santamaria S., David Cuesta-Segura A. &amp; Guardia L. 2020 a. New and remarkable species of Laboulbeniales (Ascomycota) from Spain. Nova Hedwigia 110 (3 - 4): 347 - 367. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / nova _ hedwigia / 2020 / 0577" type="journal article" year="2020">
Santamaria 
<emphasis box="[776,834,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2020a
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The number and origin of the perithecial basal cells in this genus is puzzling because there seems to be four rather of the typical three (i.e., m, n, and n’).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1251,1387,1413]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1251,1387,1413]" box="[189,1251,1387,1413]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
